==Italian==

===Etymology===
From {{der|it|VL.|*essere}}, from {{inh|it|la|esse}}, present active infinitive of {{m|la|sum||I am}}, from {{inh|it|itc-pro|*ezom}}, from {{inh|it|ine-pro|*h₁ésti||I am, I exist}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈɛs.se.re/|[ˈɛs̪s̪er̺e]|lang=it}}
* {{audio|It-essere.ogg|Audio|lang=it}}
* {{rhymes|ɛssere|lang=it}}
* {{it-stress|èssere}}
* {{hyphenation|es|se|re|lang=it}}

===Verb===
{{it-verb}}

# {{lb|it|intransitive|indicating existence, identity, location, or state}} to [[be]]
# {{lb|it|auxiliary|used to form composite past tense of many intransitive verbs}} to have (done something); to [[be]] in the state of having (done something); ''See [[:Category:Italian verbs taking essere as auxiliary|Category:Italian verbs taking essere as auxiliary]].''
# {{lb|it|impersonal|of a duration of time since an event}} to have [[pass]]ed

====Usage notes====
The present participle {{m|it|essente}} is very rare, and is usually replaced with {{m|it|stante}}, the present participle of {{m|it|stare}}. Similarly the past participle {{m|it|essuto}} has disappeared, with {{m|it|stato}}, the past participle of {{m|it|stare}}, being used instead.<ref>[http://dizionari.hoepli.it/Dizionario_Italiano/parola/essuto.aspx?idD=1&Query=essuto&lettera=E]</ref>

